\begin_body

\begin_layout Chapter
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Electrorehology effect
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(ER) phenomena, discovered by
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Winslow1949"

\end_inset

 at 1949, will be the scope of this research; with a special emphasis into
 the micro flow scale domain.
 The effect causes the Electrorehology Fluid
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(ERF) to change its viscosity up to solid-like state, through the application
 of a respective electrical field.
 The unique ability to change viscosity with fast response times, provide
 new tools and solutions for dampers, actuators and clutches.
 As an example, works on micro-fluidic applications implement the so-called
 "giant" ERF (GERF) effect discover by
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Wen2003a"

\end_inset

 2003 and implemented into GERF micro-valves as recently shown by
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Wang2011"

\end_inset

.
 ERF are suspensions of a dielectric fluid and active dipole particles.
 The ERF particles' diameter are about 10 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

m 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Gawade:2012"

\end_inset

, and for GERF the scale is in the nanometer regime 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Wen:2003a"

\end_inset

.
 Advances in applications and new requested features pose requirements upon
 the ERF as to operate with less volume flow and hence smaller particle
 diameter.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The present study, therefore, will explore the phenomena of GERF in the
 micro scale domain.
 The research will be preformed using the Micro Particle Image Velocimetry(
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

PIV) technique.
 The micro scale domain pose many difficulties.
 The main obstacle is the observation capability of the flow in a very small
 area.
 Nano-sized diameter particles-tracking or finding common behaviors at that
 scale with regular techniques such as SEM
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(scanning electron microscope), Rheometers.
 etc; are not efficient enough.
 With the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

PIV method, it is possible to obtain a velocity field of the general motion
 of the fluid.
 Further more, it is possible to obtain separate information with respect
 to the carrier fluid and the acting particles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This work aims to to identify ERF/GERF properties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The study will include the preparation of the experimental setup and the
 process procedure, Measurement equipment and related software , and specific
 methods to obtain the ERF controlling properties in the micro domain.
 Ultimately, we would like to use these techniques to identify new phenomena.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
 
\end_layout

